Work Guide: Classical Cryptography

Part 1: Research Topics
In this section, you will research various classical cryptography topics. Each topic has a set of questions to guide your learning. Avoid repetition and ensure that the questions are slightly different for each topic.

1. The Shift Cipher
What is the shift cipher and how does it work?
How can you encrypt and decrypt messages using the shift cipher?
What are the limitations and vulnerabilities of the shift cipher?
Can you provide an example of a real-world application of the shift cipher?
How does the shift cipher relate to modular arithmetic?

2. The Substitution Cipher
What is the substitution cipher and how does it differ from the shift cipher?
How can you create a substitution cipher using a keyword or a random permutation?
What are the advantages and disadvantages of the substitution cipher?
How can frequency analysis be used to break a substitution cipher?
Can you provide an example of a historical use of the substitution cipher?

3. The Affine Cipher
What is the affine cipher and how does it combine the shift and substitution ciphers?
How can you encrypt and decrypt messages using the affine cipher?
What are the advantages and vulnerabilities of the affine cipher?
How can you break the affine cipher using known plaintext attacks?
Can you provide an example of a practical use of the affine cipher?

4. The Hill Cipher
What is the Hill cipher and how does it differ from previous ciphers?
How can you encrypt and decrypt messages using the Hill cipher?
What are the advantages and limitations of the Hill cipher?
How does the Hill cipher utilize matrix operations?
Can you provide an example of a real-world application of the Hill cipher?

5. The Permutation Cipher
What is the permutation cipher and how does it work?
How can you encrypt and decrypt messages using the permutation cipher?
What are the strengths and weaknesses of the permutation cipher?
How can you break the permutation cipher using brute force or frequency analysis?
Can you provide an example of a historical use of the permutation cipher?

6. LFSR Stream Cipher
What is an LFSR stream cipher and how does it generate a keystream?
How can you encrypt and decrypt messages using an LFSR stream cipher?
What are the advantages and vulnerabilities of an LFSR stream cipher?
How can you break an LFSR stream cipher using known plaintext attacks?
Can you provide an example of a modern use of an LFSR stream cipher?

Part 2: Cryptanalysis Research
In this section, you will research various cryptanalysis techniques for classical ciphers. Each topic has a set of questions to guide your learning.

1. Introduction to Cryptanalysis
What is cryptanalysis and why is it important in cybersecurity?
What are the different types of cryptanalysis techniques?
How does cryptanalysis differ from cryptography?
Can you provide an example of a famous cryptanalysis success story?
What are the ethical considerations in cryptanalysis?

2. The Shift Cipher
How can you break the shift cipher using brute force?
What is the vulnerability of the shift cipher to frequency analysis?
How can you improve the security of the shift cipher?
Can you provide an example of a real-world attack on the shift cipher?
What are the limitations of cryptanalysis on the shift cipher?

3. The Affine Cipher
How can you break the affine cipher using known plaintext attacks?
What is the vulnerability of the affine cipher to modular inverses?
How can you improve the security of the affine cipher?
Can you provide an example of a real-world attack on the affine cipher?
What are the limitations of cryptanalysis on the affine cipher?

4. The Substitution Cipher
How can you break the substitution cipher using frequency analysis?
What is the vulnerability of the substitution cipher to known plaintext attacks?
How can you improve the security of the substitution cipher?
Can you provide an example of a real-world attack on the substitution cipher?
What are the limitations of cryptanalysis on the substitution cipher?

5. The Hill Cipher
How can you break the Hill cipher using matrix algebra?
What is the vulnerability of the Hill cipher to key length?
How can you improve the security of the Hill cipher?
Can you provide an example of a real-world attack on the Hill cipher?
What are the limitations of cryptanalysis on the Hill cipher?

6. The Permutation Cipher
How can you break the permutation cipher using brute force or frequency analysis?
What is the vulnerability of the permutation cipher to known plaintext attacks?
How can you improve the security of the permutation cipher?
Can you provide an example of a real-world attack on the permutation cipher?
What are the limitations of cryptanalysis on the permutation cipher?

7. LFSR Stream Cipher
How can you break an LFSR stream cipher using known plaintext attacks?
